# Instamojo Payment Request API Integration

Replace the existing scattered payment routes with a clean, spec-compliant Instamojo integration using the Payment Request API. The old routes used `purchases` collection and a callback redirect flow; the new design uses a dedicated `payments` collection and a dedicated success page.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **New Credentials Needed**: The existing [.env.local](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/.env.local) will have the old Instamojo credentials (`INSTAMOJO_API_KEY`, `INSTAMOJO_AUTH_TOKEN`, `INSTAMOJO_SALT`, `INSTAMOJO_ENDPOINT`) completely removed. You will need to provide your new credentials after the implementation. Placeholder variables will be added.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change — Old API Routes Removed**: The routes at `/api/payment/instamojo`, `/api/payment/callback`, and `/api/payment/webhook` will be deleted and replaced by `/api/create-payment`. The test purchase button already references the old route — that will be updated.

> [!WARNING]
> **New Appwrite Collection Required**: The spec requires saving payment data to a `payments` collection (distinct from the existing `purchases` collection). You must **manually create a `payments` collection** in your Appwrite console with these attributes:
> - `userId` (String, required)
> - `paymentId` (String, required)
> - `paymentRequestId` (String, required)
> - `amount` (Float, required)
> - `status` (String, required)
> - `productName` (String, required)
> - `createdAt` (Integer, required)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Environment Variables

#### [MODIFY] [.env.local](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/.env.local)
- Remove `INSTAMOJO_API_KEY`, `INSTAMOJO_AUTH_TOKEN`, `INSTAMOJO_SALT`, `INSTAMOJO_ENDPOINT` (old credentials)
- Add fresh placeholder keys: `INSTAMOJO_API_KEY=`, `INSTAMOJO_AUTH_TOKEN=`
- User to fill in new credentials after implementation

