### New Payment API Route

#### [NEW] [create-payment/route.ts](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/app/api/create-payment/route.ts)
- POST handler that accepts `{ testId, userId, amount, userName, userEmail, userPhone }`
- Sends a POST to `https://test.instamojo.com/api/1.1/payment-requests/` with:
  - `purpose: "NCET Ready Test"`
  - `amount` from request body
  - `redirect_url: https://www.ncetbuddy.in/payment-success`
  - Headers: `X-Api-Key` and `X-Auth-Token` from env vars
- Returns `{ success: true, paymentUrl: payment_request.longurl }`

---

### Types

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/types/index.ts)
- Add `productName?: string` field to the [Purchase](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/types/index.ts#33-43) interface
- Add new [Payment](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/lib/appwrite-db.ts#888-902) interface with: `id, userId, paymentId, paymentRequestId, amount, status, productName, createdAt`

---

### Appwrite DB Layer

#### [MODIFY] [appwrite-db.ts](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/lib/appwrite-db.ts)
- Add `createPaymentRecord(data)` function — writes to `payments` collection using admin SDK
- Add `getUserPayments(userId)` function — queries `payments` collection for completed payments
- Add `hasUserPaidForProduct(userId, productName)` — checks if payment exists for a product

---

### Payment Success Page

#### [NEW] [payment-success/page.tsx](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/app/payment-success/page.tsx)
- Reads query params: `payment_id`, `payment_request_id`, `payment_status`
- If `payment_status === "Credit"`:
  - Calls server action / API to write to `payments` collection
  - Shows success UI and links back to tests
- Otherwise shows failure UI

---

### Frontend — Tests Page

#### [MODIFY] [tests/page.tsx](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/app/dashboard/tests/page.tsx)
- [handleBuyNow](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/app/dashboard/tests/page.tsx#87-128) now calls `/api/create-payment` with `{ testId, userId, amount: test.price, ... }`
- On success, `window.location.href = data.paymentUrl`
- Access check uses new `payments` collection via `hasUserPaidForProduct`

---

### Test Access Gate (Optional Enhancement)

#### [MODIFY] [tests/[testId]/page.tsx](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/src/app/dashboard/tests/[testId]/page.tsx)
- Before rendering test, check `payments` collection for a completed `"NCET Ready Test"` payment
- If no payment found, show purchase CTA instead of test content

