## Verification Plan

### Automated (Build Check)
```bash
cd /Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5
npm run build
```
This will catch TypeScript errors, missing imports, and broken routes.

### Manual Verification (After you provide new credentials)
1. Start the dev server: `npm run dev`
2. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/dashboard/tests`
3. Click "Buy Now" on a premium test — should redirect to Instamojo payment page
4. Complete payment in Instamojo sandbox → should redirect to `https://www.ncetbuddy.in/payment-success`
5. Verify Appwrite `payments` collection has a new document with status `Credit`
6. Reload test list — purchased test should show "Start Test" instead of "Buy Now"

> [!NOTE]
> Since you'll be providing new API credentials, I'll leave the `INSTAMOJO_API_KEY` and `INSTAMOJO_AUTH_TOKEN` as empty placeholders in [.env.local](file:///Users/rounakpaul/ncetbuddy-ed-tech-5/.env.local). Fill them in before testing the payment flow end-to-end.
